KAGISO cops in Mogale City are looking for thugs who hijacked a truck full of groceries on 30 August. Police spokesman Captain Solomon Sibiya said the truck was on Kafue Street in Tshepisong near Kagiso, when two unknown suspects, one armed with a firearm, confronted the driver and his assistant. “The armed suspect pointed a firearm at the complainants and ordered them to stop.” Anyone with information about the two men should call Kagiso cops on 011 696 9065 or Lieutenant-Colonel Jerry Ngobeni on 082 461 3109.